-- Dubai lender ENBD revises NIM guidance up to 2.7-2.8 pct
-- By David French
-- Thu Jul 24, 2014 03:28AM EDT
-- None



DUBAI, July 24 (Reuters) - Emirates NBD <ENBD.DU>, Dubai's largest lender, has revised upwards its net interest margin (NIM) guidance for 2014, a results presentation from the bank showed On Thursday.

The bank now expects NIM - the amount it makes on its lending above the original cost of funds - of between 2.7 and 2.8 percent, up from the previous guidance of 2.5-2.6 percent. ENBD cited "successful balance sheet optimisation" for the change. It did not elaborate.